#X obj 211 419 f2s~;
#X text 49 40 And now for more trigonometric functions. We also try the 'atan' (arc tangent) as an alternative to 'tanh'. We can compare them. They are similar \, but atan outputs from -pi/2 to pi/2 \, so we need to normalize and divide it by half pi. The arc tangent is the second mode of [drive~] that we'll see in detail soon., f 52;
